{"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SwiftDataIntegration","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleDelegate"],"title":"Essentials","generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/GettingStarted","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Set up Ensembles to sync a Core Data or SwiftData persistent store across devices.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ensembles\/gettingstarted"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ensembles synchronizes SQLite stores by recording local changes as events and exchanging them through a cloud backend. It works with both Core Data and SwiftData.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using SwiftData?"}]},{"text":" See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SwiftDataIntegration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for a complete guide — you never need to touch Core Data directly.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This guide covers Core Data setup, starting with a complete working example using ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Add-Ensembles-to-Your-Project","text":"Add Ensembles to Your Project","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the Ensembles package to your ","type":"text"},{"code":"Package.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or via Xcode’s package dependencies:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["https:\/\/github.com\/mentalfaculty\/Ensembles-3.git"],"syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Import the core module and one cloud backend:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import Ensembles","import EnsemblesCloudKit   \/\/ or EnsemblesLocalFile, EnsemblesMemory"],"syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Complete-Example-Core-Data-with-CloudKit","text":"Complete Example: Core Data with CloudKit","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here’s a complete, working setup for a SwiftUI app that syncs via CloudKit. This uses ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","isActive":true},{"text":", which creates the Core Data stack for you and syncs automatically.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"1-Create-Your-Core-Data-Model","text":"1. Create Your Core Data Model","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode, add a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".xcdatamodeld"},{"type":"text","text":" file to your project (e.g., "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Model.xcdatamodeld","type":"text"}]},{"text":"). Define your entities as usual. For this example, we’ll assume a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Note"},{"type":"text","text":" entity with "},{"code":"title","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (String) and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"uniqueID"},{"type":"text","text":" (String) attributes."}]},{"anchor":"2-Define-Your-Model-with-Syncable","type":"heading","text":"2. Define Your Model with `Syncable`","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For deduplication, conform your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NSManagedObject"},{"text":" subclass to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol and specify which property holds the global identifier. A UUID assigned at creation time is usually the best choice:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import CoreData","import Ensembles","","class Note: NSManagedObject, Syncable {","    static let globalIdentifierKey = \"uniqueID\"","    @NSManaged var uniqueID: String","    @NSManaged var title: String","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A global identifier ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must never change"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" once it has been assigned. Changing it after sync has begun will cause duplicates or data loss.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use a fixed, meaningful value instead of a UUID for singleton objects or reference data like tags, where two devices might independently create the same logical object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"3. Set Up the Container","type":"heading","anchor":"3-Set-Up-the-Container"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftUI","import Ensembles","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    let syncContainer: CoreDataEnsembleContainer","","    init() {","        \/\/ The model URL points to the .momd bundle compiled from your .xcdatamodeld","        let modelURL = Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"Model\", withExtension: \"momd\")!","","        \/\/ This creates a full Core Data stack automatically:","        \/\/ - SQLite store at Application Support\/MyNotes.sqlite","        \/\/ - Main-queue viewContext for your UI","        \/\/ - Auto-sync on save, on app activation, and on a 5-minute timer","        let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","            name: \"MyNotes\",","            modelURL: modelURL,","            cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","                ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.example.mynotes\"","            )","        )!","","        self.syncContainer = container","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            ContentView()","                .environment(","                    \\.managedObjectContext,","                    syncContainer.viewContext","                )","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s the complete setup. The container discovers "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable"},{"type":"text","text":" conformances automatically, attaches to the cloud, and begins syncing. Remote changes are merged into "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"viewContext"},{"type":"text","text":" so your UI stays up to date."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"4-Respond-to-Events-Optional","text":"4. Respond to Events (Optional)","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Called after remote changes are merged into viewContext","container.didSaveMergeChanges = { notification in","    print(\"Merged remote changes\")","}","","\/\/ Called if a sync fails","container.didEncounterError = { error in","    print(\"Sync error: \\(error)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Using-a-Custom-Store-Location","text":"Using a Custom Store Location","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need control over where the SQLite file lives, pass an explicit ","type":"text"},{"code":"storeURL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let appSupport = FileManager.default.urls(","    for: .applicationSupportDirectory, in: .userDomainMask",").first!","let storeURL = appSupport.appendingPathComponent(\"MyApp\/data.sqlite\")","try FileManager.default.createDirectory(","    at: storeURL.deletingLastPathComponent(),","    withIntermediateDirectories: true",")","","let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MyNotes\",","    storeURL: storeURL,","    modelURL: Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"Model\", withExtension: \"momd\")!,","    cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","        ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.example.mynotes\"","    )",")!"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Working-with-an-Existing-Core-Data-Stack","text":"Working with an Existing Core Data Stack","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you already have an ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSPersistentContainer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", pass it in directly:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    persistentContainer: myPersistentContainer,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Or if you have an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSManagedObjectContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MyNotes\",","    viewContext: myContext,","    persistentStoreURL: myStoreURL,","    managedObjectModel: myContext.persistentStoreCoordinator!.managedObjectModel,","    managedObjectModels: nil,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"level":2,"text":"Auto-Sync Configuration","type":"heading","anchor":"Auto-Sync-Configuration"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Control when syncing occurs with ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/AutoSyncPolicy","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let config = EnsembleContainerConfiguration(","    autoSyncPolicy: [.onSave, .onTimer],   \/\/ Sync on save and timer, not on activation","    timerInterval: 30                       \/\/ Timer fires every 30 seconds",")","let container = CoreDataEnsembleContainer(","    name: \"MyNotes\",","    modelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: cloudFS,","    configuration: config",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set ","type":"text"},{"code":"autoSyncPolicy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"code":".manual","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and call ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer\/sync()","isActive":true},{"text":" yourself for full control over timing.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Backward-Compatibility-with-Ensembles-2","text":"Backward Compatibility with Ensembles 2","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you’re transitioning from Ensembles 2 and some users may still be on E2, set the compatibility mode:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = EnsembleContainerConfiguration(","    compatibilityMode: .ensembles2Compatible",")"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This restricts exports to formats that Ensembles 2 peers can parse. Switch to ","type":"text"},{"code":".ensembles3","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (the default) once all users have upgraded.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"The-Manual-Way-CoreDataEnsemble","text":"The Manual Way: CoreDataEnsemble","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For more control over the sync lifecycle, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble","isActive":true},{"text":" directly. This is useful when you need to manage attach\/detach timing, handle specific delegate methods, or integrate with a complex Core Data stack.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Create-and-Attach","text":"Create and Attach","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import Ensembles","import EnsemblesCloudKit","","\/\/ Get the store URL from your persistent store coordinator","let store = persistentStoreCoordinator.persistentStores.first!","let storeURL = store.url!","let modelURL = Bundle.main.url(forResource: \"Model\", withExtension: \"momd\")!","","let ensemble = CoreDataEnsemble(","    ensembleIdentifier: \"MyNotes\",","    persistentStoreURL: storeURL,","    managedObjectModelURL: modelURL,","    cloudFileSystem: CloudKitFileSystem(","        ubiquityContainerIdentifier: \"iCloud.com.example.mynotes\"","    )",")","ensemble?.delegate = self","","\/\/ Attach registers this device in the cloud","try await ensemble?.attachPersistentStore()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/ensembleIdentifier","isActive":true},{"text":" must be the same on all devices that should sync together. If you have multiple persistent stores, create one ensemble per store with a unique identifier.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Avoid saving to the persistent store while attaching. If a save is detected, attachment will fail with an error and you will need to retry.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Sync-Changes","text":"Sync Changes","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Call ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/sync(options:)","isActive":true},{"text":" periodically — for example, when the app enters the foreground, on a timer, or in response to a push notification:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["try await ensemble?.sync()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A sync downloads remote events, replays them into the local store, and uploads new local events. Sync errors are usually transient — just retry later.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Handle-the-Delegate","text":"Handle the Delegate","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Implement ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleDelegate","isActive":true},{"text":" to respond to sync events. The most important method merges remote changes into your main context:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["extension AppDelegate: CoreDataEnsembleDelegate {","    func coreDataEnsemble(","        _ ensemble: CoreDataEnsemble,","        didSaveMergeChangesWith notification: Notification","    ) {","        viewContext.perform {","            self.viewContext.mergeChanges(fromContextDidSave: notification)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If your ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSManagedObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" subclasses conform to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/Syncable","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", you don’t need to implement ","type":"text"},{"code":"globalIdentifiersForManagedObjects","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the ensemble discovers identifier properties automatically. You only need the delegate method if you use ","type":"text"},{"code":"CoreDataEnsemble","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" directly without ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsembleContainer","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"tip","name":"Tip"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Other delegate methods let you:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Inspect and repair merge data","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" before it’s committed ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shouldSaveMergedChangesIn:reparationContext:"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Handle save failures","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" during merging ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"didFailToSaveMergedChangesIn:error:reparationContext:"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"React to forced detaches","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" caused by identity changes or data corruption ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"didDetachWithError:"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/ConflictResolution","isActive":true},{"text":" for more on conflict handling and the reparation context.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Detach","text":"Detach","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To stop syncing, detach from the cloud:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["try await ensemble?.detachPersistentStore()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This removes local sync data (event logs and metadata). The persistent store itself is not affected. You can re-attach later to resume syncing.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Seed-Policies","text":"Seed Policies","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter controls how existing data in the store is handled during attachment:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy\/mergeAllData"},{"type":"text","text":" (default) — Imports local data so it can be merged with data from other devices."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SeedPolicy\/excludeLocalData"},{"type":"text","text":" — Ignores local data. Use this when you want to start fresh from cloud data."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Sync-Options","type":"heading","text":"Sync Options","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For advanced control, pass ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/SyncOptions","isActive":true},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Download only — don't integrate or upload","try await ensemble?.sync(options: .cloudFileRetrievalOnly)","","\/\/ Force a rebase to compact sync history","try await ensemble?.sync(options: .forceRebase)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Process-Pending-Changes","type":"heading","text":"Process Pending Changes","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On iOS, the app may be suspended before Ensembles finishes recording a save. Call "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/processPendingChanges()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" — for example, in a background task — to ensure all changes are fully stored:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["try await ensemble?.processPendingChanges()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Monitor Activity","anchor":"Monitor-Activity","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Track long-running operations via ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/currentActivity","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Ensembles\/documentation\/Ensembles\/CoreDataEnsemble\/activityProgress","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or observe these notifications:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"coreDataEnsembleDidBeginActivity","type":"codeVoi